This paper deals with the problem of energy management in wireless sensor networks, which is a common topic in the field of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The focus on reliability and the stochastic nature of energy harvesting also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). The use of optimization techniques and decision-making algorithms points towards information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the use of linear value approximation and online learning techniques suggests a connection to statistical learning (cs.LG).
